info.senderName: NWS LaCrosse (Southwestern Wisconsin, Southeastern Minnesota, and Northeast Iowa)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued October 26 at 8:52PM CDT until October 30 at 8:12AM CDT by NWS LaCrosse
info.description: ...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Wisconsin... Black River Near Galesville affecting La Crosse and Trempealeau Counties. Additional river and weather information is available at www.weather.gov/lacrosse. The next statement will be issued Friday morning at 1100 AM CDT. && ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL MONDAY MORNING... * WHAT...Moderate flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Black River near Galesville. * WHEN...Until Monday morning. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 7:00 PM CDT Thursday the stage was 10.3 feet. - Bankfull stage is 10.0 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to rise above flood stage late this evening to a crest of 14.0 feet early Saturday morning. It will then fall below flood stage Sunday evening. - Flood stage is 12.0 feet. - Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 14.0 feet on 04/03/1952. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
